== Description ==

The '''Arch StructuralSystem''' tool creates a structural system from a selected [[Arch_Structure|structure]] object and one or more [[Arch_AxisSystem|axis systems]]. It distributes the structure along the axes, making it easy to create repetitive structures like columns or beams aligned to a grid.

== Usage ==

# Select an [[Arch_Structure|Arch Structure]] object.
# Select one or more [[Arch_AxisSystem|Arch AxisSystems]] to define the grid layout.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → Structure Tools → [[Image:Arch_StructuralSystem.svg|16px]] Structural System}} option from the menu.
# The structural system is created, distributing the structure along the axes.

== Notes ==

* The resulting structural system maintains a relationship with the axis system.
* Each axis intersection point hosts a copy of the structure object.
* The position of the original structure object relative to the origin is taken into account.


